< Review>
I've waited a while to write this review. I had a crown put in on one of my molars. The procedure was quick, but pain after it lasted over a month. I had to go to an endodontist for consultation to get a root canal because of that. I came back to get the bite adjusted, and they just adjusted it too much. A year later I have a crown that perforated since the occlusal surface became too thin from adjustment. The crown now needs to be replaced.

It's not just the quality of care that I am unhappy about, but also how they handled the payment. I overpaid during the initial visit, and my insurance covered more resulting in a refund due to me. It took me a month and multiple emails and phone calls to the practice to get the refund even after they received the payment from the insurance and deposited into their bank account (this information was provided by the dental insurance confirming that the check cleared). I kept getting vague answers why my refund was being delayed, but finally got the refund.

An extra star is for dental assistants who truly appeared to want to do the right thing.

Looking back, I should never have selected this dental practice for my care.< /Review>

I am having a friendly conversation with staff as usual and after finding out where I work, the dentist assistant tells me she forgot something, then lied to me and said that the doctor overheard our conversation. The desk assistant told me that the dental assistant was the one who reported it which was already obvious since she suddenly forgot something. Then the dental assistant told me I had to leave because of where I work and because I mentioned that I heard we are supposed to be getting tested. I explained to her that I never cared for any known covid patients and that everyone is getting tested for the safety of the patients not because I‚Äôm suspected of having covid or have been exposed. I was told that I still need to leave and I can come back in two weeks. I walk out of the room and it‚Äôs a ghost town. This two week rule makes no sense because I never cared for anyone with covid that I know of and I will still be working at my job in two weeks. I know that if I did come back, I would receive very minimal care based on their reactions so I will not be coming back. I understand you guys are afraid and scared, but you guys need to understand that you will be caring for people who are not as transparent as I am and you guys should better prepare yourselves. If you want to deny dental care to healthcare workers then be up front about it, please state that or at least have a questionnaire so we don‚Äôt have to schedule time out of our lives to get there and feel the way that you made me feel. Also, educate yourselves. There are many people that work in the medical field and those people are aware that coming into contact with someone who has covid will be inevitable. Those people also know that wearing PPE correctly will protect you from this virus. Which is why many of our healthcare workers are not getting the virus. The lady at the front desk was not even wearing a mask. This pandemic is not going anywhere anytime soon. Educate yourselves more on transmission prevention, be transparent with your customers, and be better prepared please.</review></record>

<rating>5</rating><Pics>None</Pics>< Text>
I grew up at this park. Before the playground and walking path upgrades.

The playground was old, the walking paths were full of troughs and hills, and the basketball hoops were always 50/50 on a net for the hoops...

Now the hoops have nets, there is a nice new playground, and the walking paths are all fresh. It's the same nice open park it's always been with a fresh coat of paint.

You can also park on the street and use the levee access to walk down to Gristmill and check out the river as well.<//Text>

This was my first time at this clinic because my Boston Terrier had a major allergic reaction to something.  I called the office and they were able to get me in right away. < Text>
I am the owner of Roxy, an all white boxer/pit mix whom is disabled by being Deaf. We had her fixed by the vet at Lemon Grove Veterinary Hospital. On November 26th 2014 we had her appointment to have the sutures removed from her stomach. We arrived on time at 12pm, prior to the appointment we were asked to put one of their muzzels on her and to show early. We did as asked and the issue was that Roxy did not want to lay down. Roxy also showed extreme fear of the vet assistants present. The assistants then asked for us just to bring her back and they can just handle her back there. We followed back with them and as soon as the Vet himself showed up, he already seemed irritated and told us we would have to go. I explained she would be more comfortable with me there at least and he insisted we leave. As soon as we made it into the lobby door way we all heard an extremely loud scream coming from Roxy followed by a loud thud sound like she was hit... my brother went to look under the door but could not see anything. I then walked to the desk to look down the hall and there I saw the Vet who I just entrusted my dog too physically kick my dog on her right side and lift her off the ground by a rope he had around her neck. I screamed at him asking what He was doing. The vet then responded, " you didn't see anything, your mistaken"... This is while he's now trying to walk her to me. I then informed him that I physically saw him and that if he doesn't know how to handle animals that he has no business being a vet. Keep kept repeating himself as I called the police for assistance. This man is a danger to animals and his assistants who stood by and watched are no better. I would like this man to be recognized as the monster he is... he should have his license revoked and he should never be allowed around animals of any type.. He has no heart if he was so easily able to abuse my dog whom is an amazing dog and loves to love, she didn't deserve the brutality she received from this so called Veterinarian.</Text>

<Date>1440384017081</Date><Review>I've been coming to this vet office for about almost 5 years now prior to new management. Never had any issues with my cats coming to see Dr. Gowda. He always recommends the best medicine for my cats and very informative about complications that may arise from playing the "wait and see game" and not taking direct action of the medical diagnosis or treatment options. This always helps me make the better decision for the health of my cats. One of my cats I've struggled for 2 yrs to fix his urinary problem so Dr. Gowda suggested radiographs be taken to make sure no stones were present and we did a urine analysis in case nothing showed up on the X-rays. Radiographs showed no signs of stones but without the urine analysis we would have never known it was crystals. The fact that he highly recommended both to ensure there was no wasted time helped, stones may have required surgery so we ruled that out first and sent the urine to the lab for testing. So we treated the crystals and changed my cats diet and now he doesn't struggle to urinate and there is not tint of blood anymore. So I wouldn't believe these bad reviews, he is always looking at my records and asking about my other cats even if they are not present for an examination. Really treats the animals with concern, and understanding the bond between client and patient has enabled Dr. Gowda to take great care and consideration for his patients. <Rate>5</Rate><Text>Don't judge a book by its cover. Despite the location and semi rugged exterior, Dr. Gowda and his team are top notch.

- Dr. Gowda is straight up and breaks everything down.
- The teams service is exceptional.  Prompt with phone calls, ready with answers, follow up calls and they truely show compassion for animals.  It's not just about money, at least I hope its not in entirety.
- The rates are very competitive.  Those without pet insurance and have limited means, try them out.

I scheduled my 9 year old Dauchsands Teeth cleaning and extractions.  My primary vet wanted over $2,000 for the procedure and that was a procedure my insurance does not cover.  I found Dr. Gowda through a friend and she has nothing but postive things to say.  That sealed the deal for me.

All in the procedure cost well over $600 for my case (varies depending on breed and condition).  I dropped my dog off in the morning and left her there all day while I was at work.  They took care of her and performed the procedure under anethsia without any issues.  I picked up my drowsy dog after work and she bounced back the next day.

3 weeks later, my same dog was attacked by a pitbul and suffered deep lacerations on her back neck. It was 10 minutes to closing time for Dr. Gowda, but he and his team stayed over 2 hours to tend to my dog.  It required another case of anethsia and stitches.  =(  My dog is a trooper to endure this type of trama.

Both case Dr Gowda and team performed as expected.  They provide clear and concise post operation instruction for care and medication administration.

5 stars!</Text><pics>None</pics>< response>

< text>
Was looking forward to checking out this restaurant, since I'm a fan of ayce kbbq. I was pretty disappointed! While the price was wallet friendly, the food and service disappointed me big time! First the meat - normal selections you would expect at an ayce kbbq so nothing special here to talk about. The extras were lacking - like there was NO lettuce!  The self serve bar was tiny and the fruits were from a can and had no fruit taste!  Second the service - the limited staff was definitely short on people so we had to wait long for the meat to come out. I sympathize with them but blame the management for it.  Over all, didn't really enjoy the experience and would NOT come back.  This is a shame since this branch is closer to me than driving out to Korea town.  Oh well, gotta go where the good food is!<//text>

<review>This is the place when people want to spend minimum money for AYCE Korean BBQ in local area. It only costs $19.99 per person to get a different kind of meat and seafood. I love to eat beef belly, rib fingers, and pork belly because they have good quality.  Also, it has mini salad bar which I love to grab tofu, fish cakes as much as I want. The service here is great, and food always cone out fast as well.  Also, beer is not expensive here for a mud size so next time I may order one as well.

It is very good place for 2 or more people to come here for BBQ because it has good environment, good quality of meat, and services.< /review>< GmapID>

<Pics>None</Pics><Resp>None<//Resp><Gmap_id>0x80c2c55d6819a0f7:0xb4cb7b906de408< /Gmap_id><review>Good food and good service. My kids loved it.< /review></record></dataset><record>
<user>104168626635912189230<//user>< username>
Bruce Wilder</username>
<Date>1514315129558</Date>< rating>
4<//rating>
< review>
Went there as part of an Christmas Office party, where our group was distributed to several tables.  The place is clean, well-designed and brightly lit, upstairs in a somewhat shabby multi-use complex.  Tables typically seat 4 around a stainless grill at the center of the table, where you cook your own meat selections.

You order meats from a long menu -- including marinated beef, pork and chicken as well as unmarinated selections like steak, bacon ("pork bellies") and shrimp.  The staff will deliver up to three meat choices at a time to the table and you share.  Standard tableware are chopsticks and a single steel tong to be used in common to turn the meat.  There's a self-serve salad bar where you can also get some grillable accompaniments.

The grill surface is stainless steel and the staff will lift it off and replace it with a clean unit after your first round of meats.  There's a button on the table to summon a server when you are ready to order a second round of meats.  Theoretically, it is all you can eat, but two rounds was all we could manage.

This was my first experience with Korean BBQ and I think the newbie would want someone more experienced along for a first ride.  How satisfied you are is likely to vary with how successful you are in selecting meats and managing the cooking process and the traditional Korean condiments.  As simple as it is -- and there's nothing complicated about laying meat on the grill and turning it over when it appears to be done -- you will want some reassuring instruction from your companions.  The staff may be used to instructing newcomers -- I don't know because we had some experienced diners among us.  Service, as far as bringing meat and clearing the table, was efficient but not particular friendly or interactive -- that might not be case if you were not part of a large office party as i was.

The apparent quality of meat was very high.  I found the marinated beef especially tasty.  I am not sure I like sharing my table with a very hot grill, but that's necessary to the experience i suppose.  Other people i know said Honey Pig is as good as it gets in the Korean BBQ category.

Pricing seemed fair.  Standard gratuities are added to the bill.</review>

109938012769769483694<//userid>
<Name>steven Lai< /Name>< time>
1483064284000<//time>
<Rate>1<//Rate>< review>
The atmosphere in the restaurant is perfect. Nice music and clean table wares. Service is average. BUT the star of any restaurant has to be the food which, at Honey Pig 2.0, is what I find very lacking in taste and quality. While the price tag seems pretty good for an average Korean barbecue restaurant, the quality is just not there.
First, let's start with the sides because that is what you will have to walk up and get it yourself in a buffet style which is fine. There are typical Korean sides such as kimchi, rice, mash potatoes, etc. what strikes me the most is the fried chicken which is stone cold. Kimchi tastes like it is bought from a store that comes in a plastic jar container.
Moving on to the meat which is very lacking in consistency. Brisket sometimes come with extreme amount of fat and no fat at all. Beef short ribs are very tough like rubber. Beef galbi came in a very strange condition. The beef itself is charred and seems like it has been partially cooked once before it was served.
Overall, the restaurant fails to highlight the most important thing, the food.< /review>

104379764189225854512< /UserId.>
<user_name>John Donovan< /user_name><date>1583418810391</date><rate>3< /rate>< Review>
Replaced garbage disposal for $500. Installed kitchen faucet that I supplied for $375, but required that my older cold water shutoff valve be replaced for $160 (was $260, but they apparently were embarrassed at their own price)

The scheduling person was exceedingly nice. I called at 11 am and they gave me a 12-4 window, arriving around 2 pm and staying for about two hours. Service was prompt, friendly,  and professional, but the cost was somewhere between pricey and a rip off. When you look at how long they spent and subtract parts, they basically are charging around $400 per hour for labor. I assume that gives them some leeway in case they have to spend more time, but geez. It's like they are charging the most they have found they can actually get people to pay once you have then on site, as opposed to just charging what it costs them to do the job.

I didn't have a lot of time to shop around, so I trusted Bonney to do a good job, based on past work they did for me, and they did seem to do a good job. But in the future, I'll need to price shop to avoid being gouged. Too bad, because they were nice to work with.

I think they know they are charging high, and they must get a lot of buyers remorse, because they make the technician call a quality assurance operator and they record you saying that you approve the work and the price. It's all very streamlined, but not a great value.  By the way,  Google showed then as 4.9 stars in reviews, but yelp was around 2.5 stars, so ... not sure why that is.<//Review>

<time>1599168906814< /time><Resp>{'time': 1600723608886, 'text': "Thank you for taking time to provide us with feedback.  We investigated your review thoroughly and it looks like we quoted you a complete shower valve and trim replacement which includes some of the piping in the wall. This is a much larger job than just a few trim pieces. When replacing a shower valve in the wall it requires cutting the wall open followed by some very precise and detailed work which often includes soldering with a live flame inside your wall. This type of work is not for the untrained or unskilled. This is one of the easiest places for there to be a leak after doing the work. In addition it is one of the worst places to have a leak because you won't find the symptoms of the leak for days and then the damage has been done. We charge according to a price book that is competitive with the market.  When we do the job we offer a permanent solution and get the work done right the first time.  All our work is guaranteed. This is not the case with many plumbers, who will continue to charge with every visit and while fixing the immediate issue, they don't necessarily fix the problem long term."}</Resp><Rate>1</Rate><gmap_id>0x809ac336b757a5d9:0x8d8824f62cb79617< /gmap_id>< UserId.>

<Review>One of our renters called on a Sunday afternoon to let me know there was water gushing out of the hot water heater.  I talked him through Turning of the gas/pilot light and the water inlet, grabbed a few tools and prayed it was a hose.  No such luck..    The hoses looked fine and the water was coming out of the jacket, along with sodden insulation.  Burst tank.  I put my tools back in the truck.  The renter started making calls thinking he would not have hot water for a week or more.
Monday we called Bonney (there was a sticker from them on the tank).  We called about  1 PM, got an appointment for that afternoon.  We got an e-mail confirming out appointment in minutes, followed at 3 PM by another introducing the Technician who would be there.   By 4 we had estimates with pictures of what needed to be done.  There was some issues because it was a non-standard instillation (it looked as if the cabinet was built around the heater)  I stopped by at 5 to find him waiting to explain it all again, it was a pretty complex job.  By 5:30 he was leaving with a signed contract, and the work was done the next day!  He definitely went above and beyond.  From doing things different from standard to work with our unusual situation (He had to cut the old heater in half to get it out), to taking requests (we wanted it plumbed in a certain way), to going beyond (that house is about to get a meter, so he did the install so it would be ready for the changes a meter brings).  He instructed the Tenant on what he might be called upon to do, and filled me in by phone.  The whole project took less than 24 hours from calling for an appointment to everything being done.  I could not be happier with the service we received.  We even got the senior discount!</Review></record>

<Date>1536725401242<//Date>< review>
Robert Castle is an awesome technician for Bonney.  After having plenty of terrible experiences with companies contracted by our home warranty company, I paid out of pocket for a second opinion.  Sure enough, the lazy guy from the disreputable company sent by the home warranty company (American Home Shield, BTW) got it all wrong.  The warranty guy's first inclination was to find service work not covered by the warranty to get cash money up front without even checking the system for the reported flaws.  Apparently, Steve from South Placer Heating and Air is clairvoyant, or an air conditioner whisperer, as he determined that the only thing wrong with our unit was a lack of Freon (which was charged last year, i.e. leak in the system), and a dirty coil, which he claims was the reason for the fan motor in the furnace running 24/7 when the A/C was not running.  Robert found real issues with the unit, all of which would be covered by the home warranty had the contractor been competent and driven enough to find them.  With the age of the system (approximately 30 years), Robert recommended a new system rather than investing over $4k to repair the current one.  We are grateful for the kindness and honesty afforded to us by Robert and Bonney.  I would give more than 5 stars if possible.  Customer service and integrity is simply too rare these days.< /review>

< review>
I had a clogged sewer and all drains in the house were backed up including the toilets and the showers. Called Bonney and they could not make it out until sometime between noon and 4:00 PM. Being as impatient as I am I called a competitor who came out within the hour. The competitor poked around in the yard looking for a sewer access port and said he thought he had found it but he was wrong. He said he would have to get someone out with a camera and they could find the access port for a nominal fee of $450 (Just to find the access port) and then they would have to let me know how much to fix the clog!!!

I told him to go away and I waited for the Bonney plumbing guys to show up. Dustin showed up after calling me to give me an exact time that he would be there. He had the camera with him and located the access port within minutes (at no charge). He then explained that he had located the trouble spot and would fix it for a fraction of the cost of the other guy. Minutes later everything was running freely and the clog was gone.

Dustin explained that the access port was made of iron and had corroded and that it was catching debris which caused the blockage. He said that he could clear the blockage and things should be fine but it could clog up again. Repeated problems might indicate the need to replace the access point with an ABS plastic one that would not clog.

The problem was cleared and we have been fine for over a week now. Drains are running freely and we are happy. If we have further problems we won't hesitate to call Bonney Plumbing again. There is still a hole in the ground where the other guy dug while trying to find the access port. It was only inches away from the actual location of the access port. (close but no cigar!!!)

Thanks Dustin H.< /review>

< text>
AWESOME, AESOME, AWESOME!!!! Bonney's estimate was quite a bit more than some of the others we received for our new whole house generator, but the difference was worth it!

Curtise arrived, found and repaired the problem, and did so at an extremely reasonable cost.

Bonny is the BEST!!!

They thoroughly explained every step of the process with us, tested everything in our presence to make sure it worked, and corrected a lot of "inconsistencies" in our overall electrical system set up that was never done (or done incorrectly) when our home was built in 1992.

they also found (and corrected) one major electrical component that could have resulted in our home burning down.

<Rate>3<//Rate>< Review>
Contacted them on 6/29 to look at my A/C. They came on 6/30 which was great. They sent a likeable tech. I told him at the door that the AC was installed in 2012 and had a 10 year warranty. I asked if he had experience dealing with warranties and he said "yes". He looked at the AC and quickly found the dual capacitor was the problem. He confirmed the unit was manufactured in 2012. He went and got a part out of his van and returned to inform me that the warranty didn't cover this part. He said it only covered the condenser coil and blower. I was charged $316 for the part. I re-read my warranty after he left and it clearly sates in bold letters ALL parts. I have called Bonney three times to get an explanation and they don't even have the courtesy to call me back. 1 star because I have to give at least 1. UPDATE: I finally heard from Bonney and they refunded my $316 so I upgraded it to 3 stars. Only because of my time and hassle, but they made it right in the end.</Review>

<user_name>Dale Lowther< /user_name>< Text>
This review is in regards to Todd Suponch and Bonnie Plumbing, Electrical, and HVAC for plumbing work performed on 9-24-2020.
Todd was my technician to install new Water main valves with a pressure reducing valve and two ball valves in an effort to reduce water pressure for the incoming water supply to my home.
This was a difficult installation as the old water valve hardware was partially buried under about 3-4 inches of soil. The pressure reducing valve took more space than the original 27 year old water valve installation, challenging the installation with very little room to fit the new valve and hardware.
Todd did an excellent job fitting the new valves in place and did a beautiful job soldering the pipes while challenged with a very difficult physical challenge working at uncomfortable angles to access the existing pipe base.  He is an excellent plumber, terrific technical skills, listens well, highly motivated, and customer friendly -- all the while representing Bonnie Plumbing in a very positive manner. If I have added plumbing work in the future, I will ask for Todd to do the work. He is a hard working employee with a lot knowledge and skills.< /Text>

<Rating>4<//Rating>< text>
We just had a new HVAC system put in, including replacing all of our existing ducting, to replace our 20+ year old system.  Matthew and Oscar came out to discuss our needs and identify appropriate systems for our home.  They took time to walk through the house, take measurements, asked us questions to understand what was important for us to have, and made suggestions about appropriate systems.  They were our last estimate and not the most inexpensive either.  What "sold" us was their knowledge about systems, customer-centric philosophy, solutions to our issue (hot and cold rooms), and helping us re-frame our way of thinking about a new system from largely being cost driven to considering how different systems can significantly impact comfort in our home.  Additionally, their warranties on parts and labor as well as their guarantees helped put us at ease.

The install happened 4 days later and just wrapped up yesterday.  It took two days to complete all of the work. Carlos and his team were knowledgeable and worked around three cats we had hunkered down in one of the bedrooms.  They worked efficiently and were able to complete the work within the two days that were estimated.  We did have one issue within one hour of them leaving because the wire nuts were slightly too big and the AC unit lost power.  Michael came out and had the issue fixed promptly.  Michael was also helpful in fixing some minor drywall/paint damage that occurred during install.

My one issue was that clean-up wasn't great on either day.  After day one, there was some light insulation debris at various places in the house.  We vacuumed.  Additionally, we found a screw that had fallen in a litter box and two nails on the floor in the house.  This was a bigger concern since we have animals.  I communicated this to Carlos after day one and he apologized.  Day two there was only some insulation around the house from the ducting install.  I vacuumed it up after they had left.

Overall, a positive experience and we look forward to using our new system for many years to come!  I will update if needed as time goes on.

UPDATE: We had to have Bonney out because they left a few lines in our crawl space and didn‚Äôt seal the space. They came out and addressed the issue and offered some compensation for the trouble of the above. The tech used our side gate to take the lines out to their truck. They came in and we concluded everything. I had assumed they secured the gate like the found it, but found out at 6pm it was partially opened and unsecured (9 hours after the initial visit). This was a major concern because our cats and dog have access the back yard and could have gotten out or something in. I emailed Bonney a number of days ago and just heard back.  They apologized said they will take the feedback and incorporate it Into training to do better moving forward. I‚Äôm less than happy about how they have taken care of our home and do hope they do better to notice the fine details.< /text>

"Professional, polite, patient,  thorough and happy to be working for Bonney"  would consistently describe the team from appointment set up, follow up through service.
The competent, efficient and likeable  serviceman Lupe Espinoza replaced a leaky instant hot water unit.  I reviewed what type of unit I wanted but clearly he had read the detailed info I had given at appointment set up, so it additionally shows that at time of appointment the customer service person listened and recorded my wishes. <userid>114715564354380270655</userid><username>Curtis Steele< /username>< time>

< rating>
5</rating>
<Review>(Edited mid-2017)
Although there have been mixed reviews, 100% of my service calls with Bonney for replacing garbage disposals at my and my mom's house, water pipes outside my house, and installation of a faucet have had excellent service.

I've seen reports that the prices are "high", but most of my service visits seemed like a bargain from the quality of service and only one visit needed. None of the replacement / service needed to be fixed nor done a second time; everything had been done right the first time and tested during the visit. The visits that were more than a day followed the same formula.

I would recommend Bonney for any residential needs. Although I haven't needed any HVAC work yet, I would feel safe recommending them as well based on the experience shown and the training their technicians appear to go through on the plumbing side.

One of my past replacements was performed by Merle (153).

Update mid-2017: another great service call - I spotted an area of water that wasn't drying up after getting out of the rainy weather. Jeremy F was able to identify where it was coming from and one of his associates with a camera was able to verify the likely cause. Although it looked like it needed some extra work to resolve, the service from Bonney continues to impress.
Ben and Kon came out to dig some concrete to access some of the previously inaccessible pipes, then replace the bad parts.
Jeremy came out for a follow up the next day. Kon and Victor came out to patch up the concrete that had to be removed.
During this whole experience everyone was very professional and there were no surprises - if they found something they weren't expecting, they reported it immediately instead of waiting.<//Review><Pictures>None</Pictures>< response>
None</response>

<Text>After contacting Bonney to inquire of a renewal of the BAM program which expired less than a month earlier, I also said we will subsequently need to have a pilot light repair. My disabled mother would be he only one home so they sent Corey. Corey told her that it was more than likely the pilot assembly needed replacement. He just so happened to have the part, (retails at Home Depot for $45.00 for the complete kit)
He then told her that since we were renewing the BAM program that we would be given a discount reduced to $45.00 for the service call.
She thought based upon his statements, that we would be paying approximately $99.00 for the BAM renewal, and $45.00 for the Service Call, and whatever the cost of labor and materials would be to install the pilot assembly. Needless to say she was completely caught off guard when the total bill came to $447.00.
A $45.00 "user serviceable" part, with our "BAM discount" cost, $338.00 to install.
From my experience, it takes about :45, to an hour to put the kit together and replace. He told her he had one already in his truck, inferring it just needed to be installed.
When I gathered all the information
I made contact immediately the following day to voice my concerns, and the receptionist, (name withheld) took information and said someone would contact me later in the day.
The following day, (day#2), having heard nothing, I called and asked for the Plumbing Service manager, he was unavailable, so I left him a voicemail, repeating my concerns and said I wanted to cancel the BAM program, and I wanted some form of reimbursement for the excessive charges, all within a 72 hour time period.
I have no doubt , that Bonney Plumbing and heating ( in this particular encounter), took advantage of a disabled Senior Citizen, and has delayed ANY contact with this customer, in hopes we will drop it, or go beyond the 3 day clause for cancelling the Service.
This is unacceptable, and based upon the Better Business Bureau's series of complaints with Bonney, it seems to be a trend or operating style which needs to be addressed, one way or another.

< Text>
I usually use Bonney Plumbing, but I needed a new water heater, so I looked around for a cheaper company. Bonney's competitor gave me a 4 hour window for the estimate appointment. The technician had poor communication skills, which really affected the appointment ($45). He gave me a quote, and then I called Bonney.

Kevin Welsh (#379) arrived for the free estimate appointment within a 2 hour window. He was the polar opposite of the competition's technician: smart, articulate, funny, clean, and professional. Bonney's quote was higher than the other company's, but I got the distinct feeling that their estimate only covered the price of the new water heater, and all the other fees would be slowly revealed over the course of the job. Bonney works by the job, not by the hour, and they clearly spell out all of the charges before they begin work.

I felt confident that Bonney would pull the right permits in a timely manner, and Kevin explained what needed to be done to satisfy Sacramento code. He had the new water heater on his truck and he installed it right then (which was great, because I couldn't wait to take a hot shower again!). He also told me about the BAM program, which saved me 15% on the job.

Kevin provided outstanding customer service, and I feel at ease knowing that the job was done professionally and that Bonney will back up their work. I learned my lesson, and I'll never shop around again -- I'll call Bonney immediately from now on!< /Text>

<user_id>101264697553007393898</user_id>< Name>
Robert Martin< /Name>
<Time>1458163167219< /Time><Rate>5< /Rate>< text>
Mr. Clinton Rasmussen was an excellent Plumber Service Technician! I rate him 5 full stars for his diligence, excellent work, knowledge and skill. Bonny Plumbing should only hire such excellent technicians and I highly recommend him and this company.

As part of the BAM plan (which I highly recommend to begin with), he fixed a clogged sink, removed calcium deposits on 5 sinks, checked all flushes, faucets and pipes. Im not sure if fixing a clog was part of the BAM maintenance but I was very happy that he did do it. Saved me so much time and trouble, Im very grateful.

What started out to be a routine maintenance check resulted in him pointing out some serious issues that would have cost me hundreds of not thousands of dollars down the road. He replaced a thermal expansion tank on my water heater that was broken. Water leaked past the safety valve so it was a disaster waiting to happen. This was a huge safety risk that I was living with completely oblivious of his presence.

Getting it off was not a simple task of using a wrench. He had to use a blow torch to expand the metal connectors so that it would release. Then he used a special tool to re-thread the connector before installing the new part straight out of a sealed box. He took time to show me why it needed replacement, indicated what a new tank would fix and prevent and even showed me the difference post-install.

The next thing he replaced was a dishwasher plastic hose/pipe. What seemed like a simple replacement was actually very complicated. The location of the pipe was under the entire dishwasher and the whole unit had to be brought out to just get to the junction point. I definitely wouldnt have been able to have done this myself.

I am a noob, yes, but with instruction I can do things... however I would have not been able to do any of this myself.

I highly recommend Mr Clinton Rasmussen (Clinton R.) and Bonney Plumbing.

Thanks!</text>

< review>
Thank you Bonney and tech, LUPE ESPINOZA, for a job well done. After experiencing a tub drip/dribble in my 60+ year old house for over a year, I finally decided it was time to fix the problem. At the same time, I began having drainage problems in the kitchen as well as needing to replace some old pipe in the kitchen. Lupe diagnosed the drainage problem and created a plan to rebuild the "pre-war" parts in the tub to resolve the drip. His dedication to the project was amazing, even when there were two trips needed to the parts place to find the necessary old parts. In addition to the clog located just beyond the kitchen sink that was cleared, he also found some blockages in the main drain that he suspected might be a City problem. Although Lupe's day started at my place at 10am, he stuck around until 7:30 pm to wait out City workers and discuss the problem with them. I really appreciated his willingness to do that instead of leaving me to try and "talk technical" with City employees -- definitely not my forte. These and a few other little extras thrown in were well worth the price I paid for the job. The quotes were fair from the start and didn't later change "due to unexpected circumstances".

Warm and personable, it was a delight to chat with Lupe as he worked. He's very easy to talk to, gives full explainations of work to be done and alternatives, and always has a few good stories to share along the way. I'm glad he's "assigned" to my place should have have any futher plumbing issues. Lupe gets a full ***** 5 STARS *****.

My only reason for the overall 4 star rating is due to the scheduling of the job. Athough this wasn't an emergency, I am a BAM member and part of that includes "priority scheduling"; it was a full week and a half from the time I called to the time Lupe could come address my issues. That amount of time to wait just doesn't seem to match up to a "priority scheduling" definition.

I would definitely recommend Bonney to others.</review>

<userid>104372663835339886413<//userid>< text>
Two days ago, our HVAC system came on for the first time this spring/summer season--and promptly died. We couldn't find the problem, so we called Bonney--at 9pm on a Saturday night.

Bonney called us back at 8am on Sunday morning (and apologized for the early call even though our message said it was ok!) and had a technician at the house by 11. Barry looked at the system and told my husband the problem was PROBABLY a horribly outdated outlet, which had blown out. He asked if my husband knew how to replace an outlet, and since he did, recommended that we replace it because he would have to charge us much more for Bonney to do it. He then promised to come back 24 hours later to make sure (a) the outlet was installed correctly and (b) that the system was really fixed (if changing the outlet fixed it).

My husband changed out the outlet in 5 minutes. The system works perfectly. Barry came back, and didn't charge us anything at all, even for the visit (since we are BAM plan members and the inspection was free in May for BAM members).

Getting on the BAM plan and using Bonney has been a great experience for us, and we are 100% satisfied with Bonney. We call them first, always, and stories like this are why.< /text>
